[Fascinating! Thanks to Vincent Deubel for responding so thoroughly and
for sharing his results with our readers in such a timely fashion.
Perhaps Armindo Filipe will share with Vincent his Portugese isolate of
WNV. If anyone knows of any other European isolates of WNV, please let
me know. It appears that West Nile virus infection in Europe is not
only emerging but may be underdiagnosed, in equids and perhaps in
humans. If anyone has a viable hypothesis as to why this may be
(ecologic degradation, decreased mosquito control activities, etc.),
please let us know. - Mod.CHC]
